<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <comment: By default filpond.js & filpond.cs uploads these files to our server asynchronously as 
    soon as somenone selects them inside our drop down. It is not enough to incorperate everything 
    we want in file prompt. It does not have any previewing or anything like that  >
    <comment: filpond.css loads the latest version of FilePond from a CDN. It is in the layout page 
    because we want it gto be avilable in every single page that we are using it on >
    <link href="https://unpkg.com/filepond@^4/dist/filepond.css" rel="stylesheet" /> 
    <comment: filpond.js this script tags ensure that they are (filpond is) loaded and runafter the 
    entire body of our page is done rendering>
    <comment: to send the file with the server form submit, we download a package from plugin library 
    from installation page on filepond a.k.a more tags; encode.js script tag, preview.css link tag,
    image-resize.js script tag & preview.js script tag. defer is added to all script tags>
    <script defer src="https://unpkg.com/filepond-plugin-file-encode/dist/filepond-plugin-file-encode.js"></script>
    <link
    href="https://unpkg.com/filepond-plugin-image-preview/dist/filepond-plugin-image-preview.css"
    rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <script defer src="https://unpkg.com/filepond-plugin-image-preview/dist/filepond-plugin-image-preview.js"></script>
    <script defer src="https://unpkg.com/filepond-plugin-image-resize/dist/filepond-plugin-image-resize.js"></script>
    <script defer src="https://unpkg.com/filepond@^4/dist/filepond.js"></script>
    <comment: Below is our own script tag which will allow us to setup the filepond library. We create that inside 
    a folder called javascript, and call it fileupload.js>
    <script defer src="/javascripts/fileUpload.js"></script>
    <coomment: this link tag includes main.css found in href route inside our layout view. rel names the link tag>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/main.css">
    <title>Mybrary</title>
</head>
<body>
    <comment: the container class is defined in the following route ..|..|public|stylesheets|main.css>
    <div class="container">
    <comment: puts all the code tha goes inside of our application before and after every single page> 
    Before
    <br> 
        <%- include("../partials/header.ejs")%>
        <comment: inner-container class is defined in the following route ..|..|public|stylesheets|main.css>
        <div class="inner-container">
            <%- include("../partials/errorMessage.ejs")%>
            <%- body %> <this line imports every single one of our pages right in here >
        </div>
    <br>
    After
    </div>
</body>
</html>